<Content
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Privacy notice for The Kaamo Club."
  lang={{ current: 'English', altHref: '/datenschutz', altLabel: 'Deutsch' }}
>
  <p><strong>Status:</strong> 2026-04-26 · Phase 0</p>
  <p>
    This policy is expanded as new features (wiki, uploads, comments, Matrix
    embed) come online. What isn't described here isn't being collected.
  </p>
  <p>
    The legally binding version is the
    <a href="/datenschutz">Datenschutzerklärung in German</a>.
    This page is provided for the convenience of the international community.
  </p>

  <h2>1. Data controller</h2>
  <p>
    The data controller (in the GDPR sense) is the operator of this site.<br />
    Contact: <code>&lt;e-mail address to be filled in&gt;</code>
  </p>

  <h2>2. Hosting and server logs</h2>
  <p>
    The site runs on self-hosted hardware in Germany.
    <strong>Cloudflare</strong> sits in front as a reverse proxy and CDN.
  </p>

  <h3>Cloudflare (data processor)</h3>
  <p>
    When you load the site, Cloudflare processes connection data — IP address,
    user agent, referrer, timestamp — to deliver the connection, defend
    against attacks, and provide caching.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Provider: Cloudflare, Inc., 101 Townsend St, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA</li>
    <li>Legal basis: Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR (legitimate interest in stable, secure operation)</li>
    <li>Privacy: <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/">cloudflare.com/privacypolicy</a></li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Own server</h3>
  <p>The server keeps the following in its logs short-term:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>shortened IP address (last octet anonymized)</li>
    <li>requested URL and HTTP status</li>
    <li>user agent</li>
    <li>timestamp</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Retention: at most 14 days, then automatic deletion. No combining with
    other data sources. Legal basis: Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR.
  </p>

  <h2>3. Cookies and local storage</h2>
  <p>
    Currently <strong>no</strong> cookies and <strong>no</strong> local
    storage are set. Should future features need them (e.g. soundtrack player
    settings), this section will be updated and consent obtained where
    required.
  </p>

  <h2>4. External links</h2>
  <p>
    The site links out to Discord, Reddit, and wiki.gg. Simply displaying
    these links does not transmit data to those services. Once you click,
    you're redirected and their privacy policies apply from that point on.
  </p>

  <h2>5. Fonts</h2>
  <p>
    The fonts <em>Xirod</em>, <em>Aldrich</em>, and <em>Rajdhani</em> are
    served locally from our own server. <strong>No</strong> connection to
    Google Fonts or any other font CDN.
  </p>

  <h2>6. Analytics, tracking, advertising</h2>
  <p>
    <strong>No</strong> tracking, <strong>no</strong> analytics software (no
    Google Analytics, no Plausible, no Matomo) and <strong>no</strong>
    advertising.
  </p>

  <h2>7. Your rights</h2>
  <p>Under the GDPR, you have the following rights:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>access (Art. 15)</li>
    <li>rectification (Art. 16)</li>
    <li>erasure (Art. 17)</li>
    <li>restriction of processing (Art. 18)</li>
    <li>data portability (Art. 20)</li>
    <li>objection (Art. 21)</li>
    <li>complaint to a supervisory authority (Art. 77) — in Germany, the data protection authority of your federal state</li>
  </ul>
  <p>Send requests informally to the email address above.</p>

  <h2>8. Changes</h2>
  <p>
    This policy is updated whenever data processing changes (new features,
    new processors, etc.). The date at the top reflects the current version.
  </p>
</Content>
